  "verificationGuide": {
    "summary": "Each entry carries a canonical COSE_Sign1 envelope (RFC 9052) over an in-toto v1 Statement payload. The chain links via sha256 of each envelope; when VAULT_SIGNING_KEY is configured, each envelope is Ed25519-signed and verifiable offline against the published verification keys. Verify the chain independently of this server before relying on it.",
    "steps": [
      "Read `integrityLevel` and `signatureCoverage`. `hash_chain_only` means no signatures — only the chain links are verifiable. `hash_chain_and_signatures` means every entry is signed.",
      "For each entry: re-derive sha256 over `integrity.coseSign1` (base64-decode first) and confirm it equals `integrity.payloadHash`. Confirm `integrity.previousHash` equals the previous entry's `integrity.payloadHash` (or null at chainPosition=1).",
      "For each signed entry: decode the COSE_Sign1 envelope, look up the signing key by `integrity.signingKeyId` in `signingPublicKeys`, and verify the Ed25519 signature over the canonical Sig_structure (`[\"Signature1\", protected, \"\", payload]`).",
      "Re-build the predicate from the entry's `payload` jsonb using the same builder the writer used; deep-equal against the decoded predicate from `coseSign1`. Divergence indicates privileged-DBA tamper of the denormalized view (also surfaced as `chainIntegrityReason: payload_drift`).",
      "Cross-check the chain length against `exportMetadata.expectedEntries` (the latest signed checkpoint position). A shorter chain means audit_vault was truncated out-of-band even though the visible chain is locally consistent."
    ],
    "embeddedKeysHint": "This export embeds the engine's active signing public key(s) at `signingPublicKeys` (keyId → base64). Convenient but trust-on-first-use: an attacker who replaces both the chain AND the embedded key gets a self-consistent forged export.",
    "oobKeysHint": "For higher-assurance verification, fetch the published verification keys out-of-band from /v1/verification-keys (or the cached /.well-known/agledger-vault-keys.json) and compare against the embedded `signingPublicKeys` BEFORE trusting any signature. Pin the public keys at provisioning time; rotation events fire on the webhook channel.",
    "offlineVerifier": "Turnkey offline verifier: `@agledger/verify` on npm (v0.1.0+). Drive `agledger-verify <dump-dir>` against a `pnpm vault:dump` output for full chain + signature + checkpoint cross-check with zero AGLedger code in the dependency tree. Pure node:crypto."
  },
